cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.RO, cs.CR 

This paper deals with the problem of pedestrian localization in depth fields using deep learning algorithms. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also discusses the use of weak supervision and synthetic data augmentation, which are common techniques in machine learning and artificial intelligence, making cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) likely categories as well. The problem of pedestrian localization can also be related to robotics and autonomous systems, making cs.RO (Robotics) a possible category. Finally, the paper discusses the limitations of hand-crafted image analysis algorithms, which can be related to computer security and cryptography, making cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) a less likely but still possible category.
